This feature-length documentary focuses on the efforts by troops in the 
U.S. military during the Vietnam War to oppose the war effort by peaceful 
demonstration and subversion. It speaks mainly to veterans, but serves 
as a ready reminder to civilians that soldiers may oppose war as stridently 
as any civilian, and at greater personal peril.
